gourmet /ˈɡʊəmeɪ/

(gourmets) 

1. ADJ Gourmet food is nicer or more unusual or sophisticated than ordinary food, and is often more expensive. 菜肴精美的 [ADJ n] 

例： Flavoured coffee is sold at gourmet food stores and coffee shops. 调味咖啡在美食店和咖啡馆出售。 

例： The couple share a love of gourmet cooking. 这对夫妇都有烹饪美食的爱好。 

2. N-COUNT A gourmet is someone who enjoys good food, and who knows a lot about food and wine. 美食家 

例： The seafood here is a gourmet's delight. 这儿的海鲜是美食家的一大享受。

